---
import PNotes from "../components/PNotes.astro";
---

<p-slide class="cover-internal">
  <h1>All together now</h1>

  <PNotes>
    <p>
      The payoff slide. Everything we saw, in one component we actually ship.
    </p>
    <p>
      Don't re-teach each feature — point at them as a chord, not single notes.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

<p-slide follow-fragments>
  <h5 style="margin-block-end: 0.8em" class="center">
    <span class="main-gradient">One component. Everything at runtime.</span> 🎴
  </h5>
  <pre
    class="small-line"
    data-label-file="article.css">
    <code style="font-size: 0.52em" is:raw class="language-scss">
    @layer components {
        @property --accent {
            syntax: "<color>";
            inherits: true;
            initial-value: oklch(0.7 0.15 250);
        }

        :root {
            color-scheme: light dark;
        }

        section {
            container: content / inline-size;
        }</code><code p-fragment style="font-size: 0.52em" is:raw class="language-scss">
        article {
            display: grid;
            gap: clamp(0.5rem, 2cqi, 1rem);
            padding-inline: clamp(1rem, 4cqi, 2rem);
            padding-block: clamp(0.75rem, 3cqi, 1.5rem);

            background: light-dark(white, oklch(0.2 0 0));
            color: light-dark(oklch(0.2 0 0), white);
            border-block-start: 4px solid var(--accent);
        }

        /* wide enough AND has an image -> media layout */
        @container content (min-width: 30rem) {
            article:has(img) {
                grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr;
            }
        }</code><code p-fragment style="font-size: 0.52em" is:raw class="language-scss">
        article:hover {
            background: color-mix(
                in oklch,
                light-dark(white, oklch(0.2 0 0)),
                var(--accent) 8%
            );
        }
    }</code>
  </pre>

  <PNotes>
    <p>
      Let it land for a second before talking — the room should feel the
      density. "This is the whole talk in 25 lines."
    </p>
    <p>
      Walk it once, top to bottom: layer, typed token, color scheme, container,
      fluid spacing, logical properties, light-dark, container query, :has(),
      color-mix.
    </p>
    <p>
      Important detail: the section is the query container, the article reacts.
      A container query styles descendants, not the container itself.
    </p>
    <p>
      The honest caveat out loud: these are modern features, so in a real DS we
      layer them as progressive enhancement.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

<p-slide all-map autoplay timing-fragments="1700">
  <h3 style="margin-block-end: 1rem;" class="main-gradient center">
    No build step touched this component
  </h3>

  <dl>
    <div timing-start="500" p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      <dt>@layer</dt>
      <dd>predictable cascade</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="500" p-fragment p-effect="from right">
      <dt>@property</dt>
      <dd>typed, inheritable token</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="800" p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      <dt>oklch + color-mix</dt>
      <dd>palette computed live</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="800" p-fragment p-effect="from right">
      <dt>light-dark()</dt>
      <dd>dark mode, one line</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="1100" p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      <dt>clamp + cqi</dt>
      <dd>fluid spacing, no breakpoints</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="1100" p-fragment p-effect="from right">
      <dt>logical props</dt>
      <dd>writing-mode aware</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="1300" p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      <dt>@container</dt>
      <dd>reacts to its container</dd>
    </div>

    <div timing-start="1300" p-fragment p-effect="from right">
      <dt>:has()</dt>
      <dd>reacts to its content</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>

  <PNotes>
    <p>
      This is the photographable summary. Reveal pairs as you name them, or all
      at once if time is tight.
    </p>
    <p>
      Land the headline: not one of these needed a compile step. The browser is
      doing the runtime work.
    </p>
    <p>Transition into section 9 — the honest limits and the close.</p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

<style lang="scss">
  [all-map] {
    dl {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0.6em 1.5em;
      margin-block-start: 1em;
    }

    dl > div {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.15em;
    }

    dt {
      font-family: var(--talk-marco-graphik-medium, monospace);
      font-size: 0.7em;
      color: var(--main-sub-gradient-fallback, currentColor);
    }

    dd {
      font-size: 0.5em;
      opacity: 0.8;
      margin: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
